Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 9b9b6750-2a62-439c-ae27-e9dbc9274d3e.20144448-0155-429d-b07c-52a04eb9cd38.prompt=Notification option\: 9b9b6750-2a62-439c-ae27-e9dbc9274d3e.3e98bc33-0636-4d4e-aa38-4addf5fd63aa.prompt=url to start check from. 9b9b6750-2a62-439c-ae27-e9dbc9274d3e.46e2aec0-2df3-447e-a9ce-4eadce2ba0ae.description=
Adds a value into the global context (available to all parent and child flows)

Input Parameters\:
keyName - the name of the context variable to use
myValue - the value to assign the context variable

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Scriptlet Example\:
[$scriptletContext putGlobal\: $keyName, $myValue];
9b9b6750-2a62-439c-ae27-e9dbc9274d3e.4b7db470-6d9b-4c92-a780-0922a5ad2cd9.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
9b9b6750-2a62-439c-ae27-e9dbc9274d3e.8a6714e4-99bc-486c-8aac-3e1225fa8087.description=Iterates through a list of values. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration. 9b9b6750-2a62-439c-ae27-e9dbc9274d3e.a7c68872-a263-492a-8cb4-e4fb80573f39.description=Check to see if the value stored in a specified key is null. 9b9b6750-2a62-439c-ae27-e9dbc9274d3e.description=
This flow crawls a website and finds pages with dead links. It then returns a report on which pages contain dead links, and what the dead links are.

Inputs\:
baseURL - This is the url to start crawling from. All pages linked from this page, or any other page given a full crawl will be crawled.
allowedDomains - This is a comma-separated list of domains that can be recursed into. It automatically includes the domain of baseURL.
notifyMethod - How the user should be given the results of the flow.

Responses\:
success - The flow succeeded, no bad links were found.
failure - The flow failed.
diagnosed - Some bad links were found.
